---
title: Amazing Apricot Chicken with Fingerling Potatoes and Green Beans
description: Chicken breasts are a reliable go-to for dinner—easy to cook and pleasing to just about every palate. But let’s face it: they can be a little boring sometimes. Which is why we’ve enlisted the help of a lively sauce made with apricot jam: it coats each bite of meat in stone-fruit sweetness and even tastes great drizzled onto the potatoes and roasted green beans on the side.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/amazing-apricot-chicken-59e91e24.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/amazing-apricot-chicken-5d0a899c19076700181115dc-99e78bcb.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 550 kcal
  fat: 20 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 290 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/amazing-apricot-chicken-5d0a899c19076700181115dc
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: North America
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 35 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve @Fingerling Potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (we'll add more to the sheet then).

Once potatoes have roasted for ~{10%minutes}, remove baking sheet from oven; toss and push potatoes to one side. Toss @Green Beans{6%ounce} on opposite side of sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, toss green beans on a second baking sheet; roast on middle rack.) Return to oven and roast until veggies are tender and crisped, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve and peel @Shallot{1}(halved and peeled). Mince one half; save the other for another use. (For 4 servings, mince whole shallot.)

Pat @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in same pan over medium heat. Add shallot and @Thyme{1/4%ounce}. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @Apricot Jam{2%tablespoon} and half the @Balsamic Vinegar{5%tablespoon} (all the vinegar for 4 servings). Simmer until syrupy, ~{1%minute}. Stir in @water{2%tablespoon} (3/8 cup for 4) and @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}. Cook until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes} (2-3 minutes for 4). Remove from heat; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

> Stir in a splash of water if sauce is very thick.

Remove thyme from pan with sauce and discard. Season sauce with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Slice chicken crosswise. Divide chicken, green beans, and potatoes between plates. Drizzle sauce over chicken and serve.